            <mods:abstract>In Beyoncé's "Lemonade," the artist alluded to her husband Jay Z’s affair with ‘Becky with the Good Hair,” as mentioned in her song, “Sorry,” which started a fire online. Many people were accused of being “Becky,” including fashion designer Rachel Roy. In the mayhem, Beyoncé fans confused Roy for chef Rachael Ray and sent angry messages to her, as well. This article is a humorous account of the true impact Beyoncé has on her fans, which came into focus after the release of Lemonade.</mods:abstract>
